               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus letter from the Herakleopolites (Heracleopolite Nome), Egypt, by which Ptolemaios informs Asklapon about the petition(?) of Hermias son of Dionysios to Komanos. Mentions Asklepiades. Summary in line 1 and the docket mention Ktesippos</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 10.7 x 29.8 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">11 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto; the summary in line 1 is in a different hand; written along the fibers on the verso in the same hand as the summary</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1 cm.; lower margin of 0.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 613 was formerly P.Duk.inv. MF74 16</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
